properties.areaDesc: Coastal waters from Cascade Head to Florence OR out 10 nm
properties.headline: Gale Watch issued January 22 at 2:51PM PST until January 23 at 12:00PM PST by NWS Portland OR
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Gale Warning, south winds 20 to 25 kt with
gusts up to 30 kt and seas 13 to 15 feet at 12 seconds. For
the Gale Watch, south winds 20 to 25 kt with gusts up to 35 kt
and seas 10 to 13 feet at 9 seconds possible.

* WHERE...Coastal waters from Cascade Head to Florence OR out 10
NM.

* WHEN...For the Gale Warning, until 4 PM PST this afternoon.
For the Gale Watch, from 10 PM PST this evening through
Thursday morning.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: GALE WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 PM PST THIS AFTERNOON... ...GALE WATCH IN EFFECT FROM 10 PM PST THIS EVENING THROUGH THURSDAY MORNING
